I'm going to talk about the joy

00:02:06.996 --> 00:02:07.896 A:middle
of discovery.

00:02:09.186 --> 00:02:11.926 A:middle
How do we get people into what

00:02:11.926 --> 00:02:14.446 A:middle
they want to watch quicker and

00:02:14.446 --> 00:02:16.546 A:middle
remove barriers to entry?

00:02:18.116 --> 00:02:20.566 A:middle
The current state of TV, well,

00:02:20.956 --> 00:02:22.316 A:middle
it's kind of tedious.

00:02:22.946 --> 00:02:24.436 A:middle
You're presented with rows and

00:02:24.436 --> 00:02:26.286 A:middle
rows and rows of content to

00:02:26.286 --> 00:02:27.366 A:middle
scroll through.

00:02:28.246 --> 00:02:31.186 A:middle
Who here has spent five minutes,

00:02:32.106 --> 00:02:34.556 A:middle
10 minutes, 20 minutes just

00:02:34.756 --> 00:02:36.476 A:middle
searching for something to

00:02:36.476 --> 00:02:36.936 A:middle
watch?

00:02:37.516 --> 00:02:40.076 A:middle
It's a common and frustrating

00:02:40.076 --> 00:02:40.566 A:middle
experience.

00:02:40.566 --> 00:02:45.276 A:middle
And in that, we've become

00:02:45.276 --> 00:02:47.786 A:middle
paralyzed by choice and robbed

00:02:47.786 --> 00:02:48.716 A:middle
by indecision.

00:02:51.156 --> 00:02:53.626 A:middle
So, that's the problem.

00:02:54.736 --> 00:02:55.966 A:middle
Now, let's talk about the

00:02:55.966 --> 00:02:56.486 A:middle
solution.

00:02:58.876 --> 00:03:01.816 A:middle
Apple TV has purposefully

00:02:58.876 --> 00:03:01.816 A:middle
Apple TV has purposefully

00:03:02.056 --> 00:03:04.896 A:middle
migrated its designs towards a

00:03:04.966 --> 00:03:07.666 A:middle
content first experience.

00:03:08.346 --> 00:03:10.006 A:middle
And all that really means is

00:03:10.146 --> 00:03:11.266 A:middle
something's on, something's

00:03:11.336 --> 00:03:11.956 A:middle
playing.

00:03:12.066 --> 00:03:13.266 A:middle
When you launch into the

00:03:13.266 --> 00:03:15.546 A:middle
application, it's alive.

00:03:16.526 --> 00:03:20.156 A:middle
So, I'm going to break down for

00:03:20.156 --> 00:03:22.576 A:middle
you how to achieve a content

00:03:22.576 --> 00:03:24.646 A:middle
first experience with some best

00:03:24.646 --> 00:03:26.426 A:middle
practices, and I'm going to use

00:03:26.426 --> 00:03:28.346 A:middle
examples from the redesign of

00:03:28.386 --> 00:03:30.616 A:middle
Top Shelf and a couple from our

00:03:30.616 --> 00:03:31.906 A:middle
own TV app.

00:03:35.756 --> 00:03:37.986 A:middle
First of all, we want to remove

00:03:38.136 --> 00:03:40.426 A:middle
barriers to entry, get rid of

00:03:40.426 --> 00:03:42.746 A:middle
any hurdles between the content

00:03:42.896 --> 00:03:43.456 A:middle
and the viewer.

00:03:44.396 --> 00:03:47.066 A:middle
This principle is why Top Shelf

00:03:47.376 --> 00:03:49.376 A:middle
has become interactive and

00:03:49.836 --> 00:03:50.826 A:middle
immersive.

00:03:51.906 --> 00:03:52.876 A:middle
Let's take a look.

00:04:13.086 --> 00:04:15.506 A:middle
So we launch into Apple TV and

00:04:15.506 --> 00:04:17.255 A:middle
we hold on a poster image for

00:04:17.255 --> 00:04:18.656 A:middle
five seconds.

00:04:18.966 --> 00:04:21.946 A:middle
After which, a trailer comes in.

00:04:21.946 --> 00:04:25.796 A:middle
And it's important to note here

00:04:25.796 --> 00:04:27.666 A:middle
that that trailer, we don't

00:04:27.666 --> 00:04:29.396 A:middle
force sound on the viewer in

00:04:29.396 --> 00:04:30.366 A:middle
this instance.

00:04:30.366 --> 00:04:32.816 A:middle
Too much sound and video when

00:04:32.816 --> 00:04:34.186 A:middle
you first launch into something,

00:04:34.186 --> 00:04:35.656 A:middle
it can be destructive.

00:04:36.586 --> 00:04:39.156 A:middle
However, we do allow people to

00:04:39.156 --> 00:04:40.756 A:middle
invoke the audio later on in the

00:04:40.756 --> 00:04:41.306 A:middle
experience.

00:04:42.076 --> 00:04:45.836 A:middle
So, the content is taking up all

00:04:45.836 --> 00:04:46.396 A:middle
the pixels.

00:04:46.876 --> 00:04:48.406 A:middle
It's filling the screen.

00:04:48.856 --> 00:04:53.996 A:middle
Next, we want to ensure that

00:04:54.376 --> 00:04:55.686 A:middle
because people are now watching

00:04:55.686 --> 00:04:57.266 A:middle
something that they can easily

00:04:57.296 --> 00:04:57.886 A:middle
interact.

00:04:59.116 --> 00:05:01.296 A:middle
Every swipe or click on the

00:04:59.116 --> 00:05:01.296 A:middle
Every swipe or click on the

00:05:01.296 --> 00:05:03.156 A:middle
remote, it adds to somebody's

00:05:03.156 --> 00:05:04.026 A:middle
cognitive load.

00:05:04.546 --> 00:05:06.436 A:middle
So we want to reduce the number

00:05:06.436 --> 00:05:08.176 A:middle
of steps it takes for them to

00:05:08.176 --> 00:05:09.906 A:middle
achieve their task.

00:05:11.256 --> 00:05:15.506 A:middle
In Top Shelf, we use a visual

00:05:15.506 --> 00:05:17.846 A:middle
hint in the upper part of the

00:05:17.846 --> 00:05:20.456 A:middle
screen, and this tells people

00:05:20.526 --> 00:05:22.406 A:middle
swipe up to enter into full

00:05:22.406 --> 00:05:22.996 A:middle
screen mode.

00:05:23.606 --> 00:05:24.896 A:middle
Let's take a look at that in

00:05:24.896 --> 00:05:25.376 A:middle
action.

00:05:26.236 --> 00:05:27.976 A:middle
The user will place their thumb

00:05:27.976 --> 00:05:30.326 A:middle
on the remote and swipe up, at

00:05:30.746 --> 00:05:33.876 A:middle
which point the dock flies away

00:05:34.236 --> 00:05:36.146 A:middle
and you're left with just the

00:05:36.146 --> 00:05:38.616 A:middle
trailer playing in all its glory

00:05:38.766 --> 00:05:39.916 A:middle
filling the screen.

00:05:41.096 --> 00:05:43.226 A:middle
So you're still actually in a

00:05:43.226 --> 00:05:45.766 A:middle
browse mode but it feels like

00:05:45.766 --> 00:05:47.076 A:middle
playback, it feels like you're

00:05:47.076 --> 00:05:48.716 A:middle
inside the movie which is really

00:05:48.716 --> 00:05:49.036 A:middle
cool.

00:05:50.506 --> 00:05:53.096 A:middle
Anywhere that we can streamline

00:05:53.096 --> 00:05:55.506 A:middle
interactions, that's a good

00:05:55.506 --> 00:05:56.686 A:middle
thing for our viewers.

00:05:57.006 --> 00:05:58.406 A:middle
So we've borrowed this

00:05:58.406 --> 00:06:00.376 A:middle
interaction from inside of TV

00:05:58.406 --> 00:06:00.376 A:middle
interaction from inside of TV

00:06:00.586 --> 00:06:02.536 A:middle
app where we use it to invoke

00:06:02.536 --> 00:06:04.446 A:middle
and hide menus in the playback

00:06:04.446 --> 00:06:05.086 A:middle
experience.

00:06:05.356 --> 00:06:07.636 A:middle
So by leveraging that knowledge

00:06:07.776 --> 00:06:09.036 A:middle
that already exists in the

00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:11.176 A:middle
viewer's mind, we're making it

00:06:11.176 --> 00:06:12.296 A:middle
easier because they don't have

00:06:12.296 --> 00:06:13.906 A:middle
to learn something from scratch

00:06:14.236 --> 00:06:15.726 A:middle
in this new context.

00:06:16.376 --> 00:06:19.276 A:middle
So now that people are

00:06:19.276 --> 00:06:21.746 A:middle
interacting, you want the app

00:06:22.656 --> 00:06:24.626 A:middle
and the experience to feel

00:06:24.626 --> 00:06:25.246 A:middle
responsive.

00:06:25.606 --> 00:06:27.686 A:middle
Speed and pacing are essential

00:06:27.686 --> 00:06:29.836 A:middle
ingredients for minimizing

00:06:29.836 --> 00:06:31.226 A:middle
cognitive load.

00:06:31.566 --> 00:06:33.636 A:middle
Try and remove latency and lag

00:06:33.766 --> 00:06:35.056 A:middle
anywhere you can in your app.

00:06:35.396 --> 00:06:37.636 A:middle
That way, it will feel dynamic,

00:06:37.636 --> 00:06:38.996 A:middle
it will feel fluid.

00:06:41.896 --> 00:06:43.736 A:middle
We also want to avoid

00:06:43.736 --> 00:06:45.576 A:middle
overstimulating people.

00:06:46.186 --> 00:06:49.356 A:middle
Closet, chaotic, and distracting

00:06:49.356 --> 00:06:51.186 A:middle
interfaces, well, they derail

00:06:51.186 --> 00:06:53.616 A:middle
somebody from their task.

00:06:53.876 --> 00:06:55.546 A:middle
Imagine if you will you're

00:06:55.546 --> 00:06:59.416 A:middle
standing in a room and 11 people

00:06:59.416 --> 00:07:01.296 A:middle
are talking to you loudly all at

00:06:59.416 --> 00:07:01.296 A:middle
are talking to you loudly all at

00:07:01.296 --> 00:07:01.596 A:middle
once.

00:07:03.146 --> 00:07:04.516 A:middle
You can't hear what any one

00:07:04.516 --> 00:07:05.486 A:middle
person is saying.

00:07:10.656 --> 00:07:15.106 A:middle
If TV app interfaces do this as

00:07:15.106 --> 00:07:17.886 A:middle
well, people can't focus.

00:07:18.836 --> 00:07:20.956 A:middle
By using too many animations,

00:07:20.956 --> 00:07:22.806 A:middle
icons, images and text styles,

00:07:24.006 --> 00:07:25.526 A:middle
it competes for somebody's

00:07:25.526 --> 00:07:26.046 A:middle
attention.

00:07:26.976 --> 00:07:28.736 A:middle
And we don't want somebody be--

00:07:28.786 --> 00:07:30.286 A:middle
to be in that competitive

00:07:30.286 --> 00:07:30.886 A:middle
mindset.

00:07:31.126 --> 00:07:33.466 A:middle
We want them to be focused and

00:07:34.446 --> 00:07:34.666 A:middle
relaxed.

00:07:38.496 --> 00:07:39.916 A:middle
Now, that we've made them in

00:07:39.916 --> 00:07:41.826 A:middle
this kind of relaxed state, we

00:07:41.826 --> 00:07:44.036 A:middle
can think about diversifying the

00:07:44.036 --> 00:07:46.466 A:middle
types of content in our UI.

00:07:47.046 --> 00:07:48.586 A:middle
And just means playing with

00:07:48.586 --> 00:07:50.196 A:middle
shapes and aspect ratios,

00:07:50.476 --> 00:07:51.716 A:middle
breaking the grid from time to

00:07:51.716 --> 00:07:52.066 A:middle
time.

00:07:53.186 --> 00:07:55.436 A:middle
In our own TV app, we've done

00:07:55.436 --> 00:07:57.766 A:middle
this by interspersing a

00:07:57.966 --> 00:08:00.126 A:middle
different kind of module in

00:07:57.966 --> 00:08:00.126 A:middle
different kind of module in

00:08:00.126 --> 00:08:02.446 A:middle
amongst the standard 16 by 9

00:08:03.256 --> 00:08:03.676 A:middle
rows.

00:08:03.676 --> 00:08:04.706 A:middle
Now, this allows us to do a

00:08:04.706 --> 00:08:05.386 A:middle
couple of things.

00:08:06.146 --> 00:08:08.356 A:middle
First, it gives us, the

00:08:08.356 --> 00:08:10.846 A:middle
provider, a place to highlight

00:08:10.846 --> 00:08:12.336 A:middle
something that's of great

00:08:12.336 --> 00:08:14.466 A:middle
importance, something that is

00:08:14.466 --> 00:08:16.506 A:middle
really meaningful that we want

00:08:16.506 --> 00:08:17.226 A:middle
you to notice.

00:08:17.786 --> 00:08:20.806 A:middle
And for the viewer, it allows

00:08:20.806 --> 00:08:23.556 A:middle
their eye a moment of pause.

00:08:24.366 --> 00:08:25.776 A:middle
As they're scanning through

00:08:25.776 --> 00:08:28.046 A:middle
these dense grids, creating

00:08:28.046 --> 00:08:30.206 A:middle
something like this gives them a

00:08:30.246 --> 00:08:31.586 A:middle
time to breathe.

00:08:31.696 --> 00:08:37.806 A:middle
We want to reduce the canvas to

00:08:37.806 --> 00:08:40.166 A:middle
simple noncompeting elements.

00:08:41.066 --> 00:08:42.576 A:middle
And this means we create a

00:08:42.576 --> 00:08:43.256 A:middle
hierarchy.

00:08:45.176 --> 00:08:47.626 A:middle
In the Top Shelf design, the

00:08:47.626 --> 00:08:49.866 A:middle
content is of highest priority,

00:08:50.136 --> 00:08:51.766 A:middle
so it fills the screen.

00:08:52.206 --> 00:08:54.556 A:middle
Then we have the app dock and a

00:08:54.556 --> 00:08:56.116 A:middle
picking row below that in the

00:08:56.116 --> 00:08:57.666 A:middle
lower third, and they're of

00:08:57.726 --> 00:08:59.246 A:middle
slightly less importance.

00:08:59.246 --> 00:09:01.376 A:middle
And by prioritizing elements,

00:08:59.246 --> 00:09:01.376 A:middle
And by prioritizing elements,

00:09:02.396 --> 00:09:04.616 A:middle
you help people to navigate.

00:09:05.956 --> 00:09:08.686 A:middle
You help people by leading them

00:09:08.806 --> 00:09:10.286 A:middle
through the experience.

00:09:14.426 --> 00:09:16.916 A:middle
Now, meta-data, it's useful but

00:09:17.156 --> 00:09:19.836 A:middle
secondary in the content first

00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:21.706 A:middle
experience of Top Shelf.

00:09:22.156 --> 00:09:23.886 A:middle
Because initially we want to get

00:09:23.886 --> 00:09:25.576 A:middle
people excited about what

00:09:25.576 --> 00:09:27.526 A:middle
they're watching, and then we

00:09:27.526 --> 00:09:30.626 A:middle
signal that there's more info

00:09:30.626 --> 00:09:31.406 A:middle
available.

00:09:32.626 --> 00:09:33.706 A:middle
Let's take a look.

00:09:55.416 --> 00:09:58.376 A:middle
So the person was inside the

00:09:58.376 --> 00:10:00.576 A:middle
full screen experience of Top

00:09:58.376 --> 00:10:00.576 A:middle
full screen experience of Top

00:10:00.576 --> 00:10:02.516 A:middle
Shelf, and they've rested their

