like.

00:32:27.036 --> 00:32:27.966 A:middle
I'll start with an example.

00:32:29.636 --> 00:32:31.916 A:middle
How many of you had sat down to

00:32:31.916 --> 00:32:33.966 A:middle
watch TV only to be presented

00:32:33.966 --> 00:32:34.786 A:middle
with something that looks like

00:32:34.786 --> 00:32:35.246 A:middle
this?

00:32:35.786 --> 00:32:37.106 A:middle
Well, we want to make that a

00:32:37.106 --> 00:32:37.856 A:middle
thing of the past.

00:32:38.586 --> 00:32:39.906 A:middle
While we're glad that your apps

00:32:39.906 --> 00:32:41.226 A:middle
are providing great personalized

00:32:41.226 --> 00:32:43.496 A:middle
recommendations, ultimately, a

00:32:43.496 --> 00:32:45.586 A:middle
screen like this isn't a content

00:32:45.626 --> 00:32:46.596 A:middle
first experience.

00:32:47.066 --> 00:32:48.516 A:middle
It can be especially frustrating

00:32:48.516 --> 00:32:50.896 A:middle
because in tvOS 13, the Apple TV

00:32:50.896 --> 00:32:51.856 A:middle
already knows who you are.

00:32:52.206 --> 00:32:53.956 A:middle
So why is it asking again?

00:32:54.956 --> 00:32:55.906 A:middle
Let's take a look at what we're

00:32:55.906 --> 00:32:56.606 A:middle
doing to help you.

00:32:57.196 --> 00:33:00.346 A:middle
We have new API and TV services

00:32:57.196 --> 00:33:00.346 A:middle
We have new API and TV services

00:33:00.346 --> 00:33:03.376 A:middle
in tvOS 13, TVUserManager to

00:33:03.376 --> 00:33:04.746 A:middle
help your profile-based apps

00:33:04.806 --> 00:33:05.896 A:middle
integrate with multiuser.

00:33:06.666 --> 00:33:07.776 A:middle
We do a few things for you.

00:33:08.566 --> 00:33:10.456 A:middle
We supply you an identifier that

00:33:10.456 --> 00:33:11.866 A:middle
represents the current user on

00:33:11.866 --> 00:33:13.626 A:middle
the TV, and we'll let you know

00:33:13.626 --> 00:33:14.806 A:middle
when that identifier changes.

00:33:15.536 --> 00:33:16.806 A:middle
This is important because with

00:33:16.806 --> 00:33:18.476 A:middle
Control Center, that can happen

00:33:18.526 --> 00:33:19.416 A:middle
even when your apps in the

00:33:19.496 --> 00:33:19.996 A:middle
foreground.

00:33:20.856 --> 00:33:22.596 A:middle
We even supply you some system

00:33:22.596 --> 00:33:24.376 A:middle
UI to help people using your app

00:33:24.446 --> 00:33:26.266 A:middle
map between our user identifiers

00:33:26.616 --> 00:33:27.916 A:middle
and your app's profiles.

00:33:29.546 --> 00:33:30.586 A:middle
So what do you have to do to

00:33:30.586 --> 00:33:31.916 A:middle
integrate with TVUserManager?

00:33:33.326 --> 00:33:35.306 A:middle
Most importantly, you're

00:33:35.306 --> 00:33:36.776 A:middle
responsible for mapping between

00:33:36.776 --> 00:33:38.516 A:middle
a user identifier and a profile

00:33:38.516 --> 00:33:39.666 A:middle
in your app.

00:33:39.666 --> 00:33:40.956 A:middle
Generally, you would want to

00:33:40.956 --> 00:33:41.776 A:middle
store this in your user

00:33:41.776 --> 00:33:43.416 A:middle
defaults, mapping each user

00:33:43.416 --> 00:33:45.016 A:middle
identifier to a profile.

00:33:45.626 --> 00:33:46.886 A:middle
It's perfectly acceptable to

00:33:46.886 --> 00:33:48.406 A:middle
have multiple user identifiers

00:33:48.406 --> 00:33:49.686 A:middle
map to a single profile.

00:33:50.296 --> 00:33:52.306 A:middle
What this means is that you can

00:33:52.306 --> 00:33:54.036 A:middle
have multiple users on a TV and

00:33:54.036 --> 00:33:55.256 A:middle
they can share the same profile

00:33:55.256 --> 00:33:56.996 A:middle
in an app.

00:33:56.996 --> 00:33:58.426 A:middle
And these user identifiers will

00:33:58.426 --> 00:33:59.766 A:middle
be unique for every developer

00:33:59.766 --> 00:34:00.066 A:middle
team.

00:33:59.766 --> 00:34:00.066 A:middle
team.

00:34:00.436 --> 00:34:02.216 A:middle
So if you have multiple apps or

00:34:02.216 --> 00:34:03.786 A:middle
extensions in your suite, you

00:34:03.786 --> 00:34:04.516 A:middle
can all share the same

00:34:04.516 --> 00:34:05.166 A:middle
preferences.

00:34:06.576 --> 00:34:07.566 A:middle
You're also responsible for

00:34:07.566 --> 00:34:08.795 A:middle
listening for changes in the

00:34:08.795 --> 00:34:09.926 A:middle
current user identifier.

00:34:09.926 --> 00:34:11.735 A:middle
I'll get into some best

00:34:11.735 --> 00:34:14.085 A:middle
practices on how to handle that

00:34:14.696 --> 00:34:14.835 A:middle
later.

00:34:15.085 --> 00:34:16.346 A:middle
It's also up to your apps to

00:34:16.346 --> 00:34:17.636 A:middle
call the methods you have to

00:34:17.636 --> 00:34:19.146 A:middle
present system UI in a way that

00:34:19.146 --> 00:34:20.166 A:middle
makes sense for your app's

00:34:20.166 --> 00:34:20.676 A:middle
workflow.

00:34:21.295 --> 00:34:22.606 A:middle
But everyone's app is a little

00:34:22.606 --> 00:34:22.956 A:middle
different.

00:34:23.025 --> 00:34:24.186 A:middle
So let's take a look at an

00:34:24.186 --> 00:34:24.626 A:middle
example.

00:34:25.656 --> 00:34:27.295 A:middle
Imagine your app puts up a

00:34:27.295 --> 00:34:28.706 A:middle
profile picker just like the one

00:34:28.706 --> 00:34:29.616 A:middle
I showed you before when it

00:34:29.616 --> 00:34:29.956 A:middle
launches.

00:34:31.176 --> 00:34:33.826 A:middle
Well, here's what you do, before

00:34:33.826 --> 00:34:35.235 A:middle
you even put up your profile

00:34:35.235 --> 00:34:36.606 A:middle
picker, you check to see if your

00:34:36.606 --> 00:34:38.166 A:middle
app has a profile associated

00:34:38.166 --> 00:34:38.835 A:middle
with the current user

00:34:38.835 --> 00:34:39.426 A:middle
identifier.

00:34:39.755 --> 00:34:41.496 A:middle
If it does, you can provide

00:34:41.496 --> 00:34:42.735 A:middle
people with the absolute best

00:34:42.735 --> 00:34:43.406 A:middle
experience.

00:34:44.485 --> 00:34:45.936 A:middle
You can just let them watch TV.

00:34:46.516 --> 00:34:47.426 A:middle
You don't have to ask them any

00:34:47.426 --> 00:34:48.036 A:middle
questions.

00:34:48.176 --> 00:34:48.985 A:middle
You don't have to show them any

00:34:48.985 --> 00:34:49.746 A:middle
selection screens.

00:34:49.746 --> 00:34:51.166 A:middle
You can just bring them right to

00:34:51.166 --> 00:34:51.716 A:middle
their content.

00:34:52.275 --> 00:34:54.646 A:middle
If you don't have a profile

00:34:54.646 --> 00:34:55.585 A:middle
saved for the current user

00:34:55.585 --> 00:34:57.296 A:middle
identifier, now is when you put

00:34:57.296 --> 00:34:58.446 A:middle
up your app's profile picker.

00:34:59.226 --> 00:35:00.326 A:middle
But when someone makes a

00:34:59.226 --> 00:35:00.326 A:middle
But when someone makes a

00:35:00.326 --> 00:35:02.006 A:middle
selection, you can ask them if

00:35:02.046 --> 00:35:03.276 A:middle
this is the right profile for

00:35:03.276 --> 00:35:04.666 A:middle
the current user with this

00:35:04.666 --> 00:35:05.176 A:middle
dialogue.

00:35:06.236 --> 00:35:07.866 A:middle
This is the UI that will put up

00:35:07.986 --> 00:35:09.566 A:middle
asking the person using your app

00:35:09.566 --> 00:35:10.566 A:middle
if they want to associate the

00:35:10.566 --> 00:35:12.146 A:middle
current user identifier with the

00:35:12.146 --> 00:35:13.416 A:middle
profile that was just selected.

00:35:14.146 --> 00:35:15.626 A:middle
If they say yes and you save the

00:35:15.626 --> 00:35:16.966 A:middle
result, they won't have to be

00:35:16.966 --> 00:35:18.046 A:middle
asked the next time.

00:35:18.146 --> 00:35:19.176 A:middle
So they can have the best

00:35:19.526 --> 00:35:20.636 A:middle
experience when they launch the

00:35:20.636 --> 00:35:21.426 A:middle
app the next time.

00:35:22.276 --> 00:35:23.516 A:middle
So how do you put this UI on

00:35:23.516 --> 00:35:23.936 A:middle
screen?

00:35:24.736 --> 00:35:25.106 A:middle
It's easy.

00:35:25.106 --> 00:35:26.556 A:middle
You can do that with

00:35:26.556 --> 00:35:27.386 A:middle
shouldStorePreference

00:35:27.386 --> 00:35:28.106 A:middle
ForCurrentUser.

00:35:29.356 --> 00:35:31.096 A:middle
And you can also let people

00:35:31.096 --> 00:35:32.516 A:middle
modify these mappings after the

00:35:32.556 --> 00:35:33.676 A:middle
fact with the Preference Panel.

00:35:34.316 --> 00:35:35.236 A:middle
You can present that with

00:35:35.336 --> 00:35:36.706 A:middle
presentProfilePreferencePanel.

00:35:37.006 --> 00:35:38.446 A:middle
That UI looks like this.

00:35:39.406 --> 00:35:40.586 A:middle
In this dialogue, you provide

00:35:40.586 --> 00:35:42.176 A:middle
the current mapping between user

00:35:42.176 --> 00:35:44.346 A:middle
identifiers and profiles, and

00:35:44.346 --> 00:35:45.716 A:middle
we'll give you back the changes.

00:35:46.296 --> 00:35:47.806 A:middle
For both this UI and the

00:35:47.806 --> 00:35:49.426 A:middle
confirmation dialogue, you

00:35:49.426 --> 00:35:51.676 A:middle
provide usernames and user

00:35:51.676 --> 00:35:53.206 A:middle
identifiers and we'll supply the

00:35:53.206 --> 00:35:56.126 A:middle
real user names in the UI.

00:35:56.406 --> 00:35:57.816 A:middle
So, like I mentioned before,

00:35:57.816 --> 00:35:58.556 A:middle
your app should be able to

00:35:58.556 --> 00:35:59.756 A:middle
handle updates in the current

00:35:59.756 --> 00:36:00.536 A:middle
user identifier.

00:35:59.756 --> 00:36:00.536 A:middle
user identifier.

00:36:01.576 --> 00:36:02.606 A:middle
You listen for changes in the

00:36:02.606 --> 00:36:03.886 A:middle
current user identifier with the

00:36:03.886 --> 00:36:04.976 A:middle
currentUserIdentifier

00:36:04.976 --> 00:36:06.146 A:middle
DidChangeNotification.

00:36:06.936 --> 00:36:08.486 A:middle
And when this happens, you're

00:36:08.486 --> 00:36:09.586 A:middle
responsible for letting us know

00:36:09.586 --> 00:36:11.486 A:middle
the new mapping by setting user

00:36:11.486 --> 00:36:13.126 A:middle
identifiers for current profile.

00:36:13.516 --> 00:36:15.886 A:middle
Since there can be multiple user

00:36:15.886 --> 00:36:17.256 A:middle
identifiers pointing to the same

00:36:17.256 --> 00:36:18.816 A:middle
profile, you may set multiple

00:36:18.816 --> 00:36:19.406 A:middle
values here.

00:36:19.896 --> 00:36:21.216 A:middle
So that's one thing you should

00:36:21.216 --> 00:36:22.246 A:middle
do when the user identifier

00:36:22.246 --> 00:36:22.716 A:middle
changes.

00:36:22.976 --> 00:36:24.706 A:middle
What else?

00:36:24.786 --> 00:36:25.736 A:middle
Well, we have some best

00:36:25.736 --> 00:36:27.416 A:middle
practices that we recommend for

00:36:27.416 --> 00:36:28.496 A:middle
dealing with profiles in your

00:36:29.476 --> 00:36:29.576 A:middle
apps.

00:36:30.506 --> 00:36:31.686 A:middle
If you have to change the

00:36:31.686 --> 00:36:33.346 A:middle
profile and the previous profile

00:36:33.346 --> 00:36:35.506 A:middle
had ongoing activity, save it

00:36:35.566 --> 00:36:36.666 A:middle
because no one wants to lose

00:36:36.666 --> 00:36:37.166 A:middle
what they're doing.

00:36:37.986 --> 00:36:39.786 A:middle
And you should also make sure

00:36:39.786 --> 00:36:41.426 A:middle
that the change is meaningful.

00:36:41.426 --> 00:36:43.046 A:middle
So if-- You should be showing

00:36:43.046 --> 00:36:43.926 A:middle
things like personalized

00:36:43.926 --> 00:36:45.856 A:middle
recommendations, and make the

00:36:45.856 --> 00:36:46.536 A:middle
change clear.

00:36:46.906 --> 00:36:48.296 A:middle
So have it have a smooth

00:36:48.296 --> 00:36:50.146 A:middle
transition and that will make it

00:36:50.146 --> 00:36:51.756 A:middle
clear to people that the change

00:36:51.756 --> 00:36:52.346 A:middle
was successful.

00:36:55.276 --> 00:36:57.216 A:middle
So what do we learn about user

00:36:57.216 --> 00:36:58.426 A:middle
profiles today on tvOS?

00:36:58.946 --> 00:36:59.916 A:middle
We learned that if you have a

00:36:59.916 --> 00:37:01.616 A:middle
profile-based app, you can take

00:36:59.916 --> 00:37:01.616 A:middle
profile-based app, you can take

00:37:01.616 --> 00:37:03.026 A:middle
advantage of multiuser to get

00:37:03.026 --> 00:37:04.666 A:middle
people better personalization.

00:37:05.256 --> 00:37:07.886 A:middle
And you can use TVUserManager to

00:37:07.886 --> 00:37:08.886 A:middle
launch your app to a content

00:37:08.956 --> 00:37:10.516 A:middle
first experience, where people

00:37:10.516 --> 00:37:12.116 A:middle
can skip unnecessary dialogues

00:37:12.356 --> 00:37:13.716 A:middle
and go straight to watching TV.

00:37:15.266 --> 00:37:16.146 A:middle
So now that I've talked about

00:37:16.146 --> 00:37:17.516 A:middle
your first launch experience,

00:37:18.006 --> 00:37:19.366 A:middle
let's talk about what you'll see

00:37:19.366 --> 00:37:20.756 A:middle
next in your app, the Tab Bar.

00:37:28.936 --> 00:37:30.366 A:middle
With the new TV app, we

00:37:30.366 --> 00:37:31.456 A:middle
introduce a new Tab Bar.

00:37:31.776 --> 00:37:33.346 A:middle
It makes navigation easy.

00:37:33.636 --> 00:37:34.956 A:middle
And it really lets the content

00:37:34.956 --> 00:37:35.916 A:middle
behind it shine.

00:37:37.816 --> 00:37:39.386 A:middle
Because it moves along

00:37:39.386 --> 00:37:40.446 A:middle
vertically with the content

00:37:40.546 --> 00:37:41.986 A:middle
rather than disappearing when it

00:37:41.986 --> 00:37:44.066 A:middle
loses focus, it's a great way to

00:37:44.066 --> 00:37:45.326 A:middle
reinforce hierarchy for people

00:37:45.326 --> 00:37:45.876 A:middle
using an app.

00:37:45.876 --> 00:37:48.286 A:middle
I'm pleased to announce in tvOS

00:37:48.286 --> 00:37:50.126 A:middle
13, everyone gets this new Tab

00:37:50.126 --> 00:37:50.936 A:middle
Bar style.

00:37:54.716 --> 00:37:55.796 A:middle
So what do you have to do to

00:37:55.796 --> 00:37:56.796 A:middle
adopt the new Tab Bar?

00:37:57.226 --> 00:37:59.026 A:middle
In most cases nothing, but

00:37:59.026 --> 00:38:00.066 A:middle
sometimes you'll want to modify

00:37:59.026 --> 00:38:00.066 A:middle
sometimes you'll want to modify

00:38:00.066 --> 00:38:01.296 A:middle
the behavior and here's how.

00:38:02.036 --> 00:38:03.286 A:middle
