00:45:20.826 --> 00:45:23.186 A:middle
So that's masking.

00:45:23.186 --> 00:45:24.396 A:middle
Let's talk about parallax.

00:45:25.156 --> 00:45:26.456 A:middle
Parallax is just a way to create

00:45:26.456 --> 00:45:27.746 A:middle
depth by moving layers at

00:45:27.746 --> 00:45:28.476 A:middle
different rates.

00:45:28.926 --> 00:45:30.346 A:middle
We do this all over tvOS

00:45:30.346 --> 00:45:30.736 A:middle
already.

00:45:30.736 --> 00:45:32.366 A:middle
Let me explain how that applies

00:45:32.366 --> 00:45:33.686 A:middle
to our layout.

00:45:34.776 --> 00:45:36.556 A:middle
The layout has a Parallax Factor

00:45:36.556 --> 00:45:37.046 A:middle
property.

00:45:37.246 --> 00:45:39.006 A:middle
It specifies how much slower the

00:45:39.006 --> 00:45:40.396 A:middle
