00:45:46.506 --> 00:45:47.546 A:middle
layout attributes and the

00:45:47.546 --> 00:45:48.866 A:middle
parallax offset property.

00:45:49.506 --> 00:45:50.746 A:middle
This specifies the distance

00:45:50.746 --> 00:45:51.926 A:middle
between the center of the Masked

00:45:51.926 --> 00:45:53.296 A:middle
Background and Masked Content

00:45:53.296 --> 00:45:54.356 A:middle
View at any point in time.

00:45:55.246 --> 00:45:56.576 A:middle
With different rates of motion

00:45:56.576 --> 00:45:57.826 A:middle
and a partially transparent

00:45:57.826 --> 00:45:59.816 A:middle
Masked Content View, you can see

00:45:59.816 --> 00:46:00.916 A:middle
how we'd be able to simulate a

00:45:59.816 --> 00:46:00.916 A:middle
how we'd be able to simulate a

00:46:00.916 --> 00:46:02.346 A:middle
sense of depth.

00:46:05.156 --> 00:46:06.706 A:middle
Finally, when combined together

00:46:06.706 --> 00:46:08.466 A:middle
with the mask, we get the wipe

00:46:08.466 --> 00:46:09.746 A:middle
effect that you saw on Felipe's

00:46:09.746 --> 00:46:10.026 A:middle
demo.

